\b\fs60 \cf2 Salted Caramel Apple:
\b0   Toss 3 pounds sliced peeled apples with 2 tablespoons lemon juice. Cook 2/3 cup sugar over medium-high heat until amber, about 10 minutes. Off the heat, stir in 1/2 stick butter and 1 tablespoon cream. Add the apples and cook until soft. Stir in 2 tablespoons flour; let cool, then add 1/2 teaspoon sea salt. Assemble and bake as for Apple Pie.\
